        <p>We used tables back in high school. Then came floats. Flexbox before it worked properly &mdash; and flex after it finally did. Then grid.</p>
        <p>Fireworks turned into photoshop, .psd became .sketch, which then became .fig.</p>
        <p>Flash faded. jQuery took over. Frameworks came and went. Browsers eventually grew web components, and the internet survived the cookie notice war.</p>
        <p>Eventually, the goal stopped being keeping up and became building things that last.</p>
        <p>My focus shifted toward semantic, accessible, performant sites designed to age slowly.</p>
        <p>Somewhere between client launches, side projects, rebuilds, and late-night deploys, I turned 36. I wear glasses now.</p>
        <p>These days I live in ☀️ Las Palmas de Gran Canaria with my beautiful wife and two rag-cats. We love the ocean, documentaries, coffee breaks and blue skies.</p>
